President Obama has released the National Strategy for Countering Biological Threats, which addresses the challenges of biological weapons proliferation and terrorism. The strategy focuses on the importance of the life sciences in combating infectious diseases and outlines actions to prevent biological threats. The United States government will work with domestic and international partners to promote global health security, reinforce norms of safe conduct, improve threat identification, reduce potential exploitation, enhance capabilities to prevent attacks, communicate effectively with stakeholders, and transform the international dialogue on biological threats.